5) Q: How do components communicate in Angular?

Answer:

Angular components communicate in different ways depending on the requirement.

For Parent to Child communication, we used @Input().

For Child to Parent communication, we used @Output() and EventEmitter.

For sibling components or unrelated components, we used shared services with BehaviorSubject.

Example:
If user profile updated in one component, we shared updated data using BehaviorSubject so other components received changes automatically.

