10) Q: Difference between ngIf and hidden?

Answer:

ngIf completely removes the element from DOM.

hidden only hides the element but keeps it in DOM.

We used ngIf when element was not needed to improve performance.

We used hidden when we only wanted to show or hide quickly without recreating the DOM.


