12) Q: Explain authentication flow in Angular.

Answer:

In our project, authentication worked using JWT token.

When user logs in:

- Login API gets called
- Backend sends JWT token
- Token stored in localStorage or sessionStorage
- Interceptor automatically adds token in every API request
- Route guards protect private routes

If token is invalid or expired, user is redirected to login page.

This helped secure the application.

