8. SUBJECT vs BEHAVIORSUBJECT 
Subject does not store old values and works only for active subscribers,
whereas BehaviorSubject stores the latest value and sends it to new subscribers immediately.

1) SUBJECT ✅

Rule:
Subscribe first → Emit later
Step 1:
HomeComponent subscribe karta hai
subscribe() ✅

Step 2:
Navbar dropdown change
next('Admin') ✅

Output:
Admin ✅

Reason:
Home already listening tha.

-----------------------------------
Subject Fail Case ❌
Step 1:
Navbar pehle emit kar deta hai
next('Admin') ❌

Step 2:
Home baad me subscribe karta hai
subscribe()

Output:
No data ❌

Reason:
Subject old value store nahi karta.




2) BEHAVIORSUBJECT ✅

Rule:
Emit first → Subscribe later
(phir bhi chalega)

Step 1:
Navbar dropdown change
next('Admin')
BehaviorSubject latest value save kar leta hai ✅


Step 2:
Home baad me subscribe karta hai
subscribe()

Output:
Admin ✅

Reason:
BehaviorSubject latest value memory me rakhta hai.

Example: 

// service.ts
import { Subject, BehaviorSubject } from 'rxjs';

// Subject
roleSubject = new Subject<string>();

// BehaviorSubject
roleBehavior = new BehaviorSubject<string>('User');

// Navbar Component (Emit Data)

onRoleChange(role: string) {
  // Emit data
  this.roleSubject.next(role);

  // Emit + Store latest value
  this.roleBehavior.next(role);
}

// Home Component (Get Data)

ngOnInit() {
  // Subject
  this.roleSubject.subscribe(data => {
    console.log('Subject:', data);
  });

  // BehaviorSubject
  this.roleBehavior.subscribe(data => {
    console.log('Behavior:', data);
  });

}

SUBJECT

subscribe() first ✅
next('Admin') later ✅

Output:
Admin


Subject Fail ❌
next('Admin') first
subscribe() later

Output:
No data


BEHAVIORSUBJECT

next('Admin') first ✅
subscribe() later ✅

Output:
Admin

Reason:
BehaviorSubject latest value save karta hai.

